{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:48:58.633Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Achieving Successful Compilation**\n\nI'm thrilled! The linting process completed without a hitch. Now, I'm shifting gears to blueprinting the `/admin/dashboard` section, which will serve as the internal control center. The focus is solely on `/admin` and `/admin/dashboard`, leveraging the private app and excluding the landing page.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:48:59.897Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Dashboard Content**\n\nMy current focus is on defining the precise data visualizations for the admin dashboard. I've broken it down item-by-item: specifically the clients overview, active projects, AI operations, and so on. I'm prioritizing real-world representation, so I've created a list of representative clients for the client overview, with data points such as region, sandbox count, and security compliance to reflect a clear, actionable overview.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:49:01.740Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Project Data Points**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the \"Active Projects\" section. I've fleshed out the data points, including client, phase, deadline, and thread load. I'm also adding action buttons for quick commands and clear status indicators, all with a focus on ease of use. The goal is to make project management streamlined and actionable for the admin.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
